f=Governance/precedent/operational/skill/precedent-skill-routing.md · p=Precedent's routing map. trigger phrases see `operational/commands/precedent-commands.md`. · h2:Where Identity Fits=Precedent identity identity content department-leader-only (board holds Governance's). Universal-only principles; tone layer. · h2:Pipeline (per live gate review)=`board receives a gate request \· \| \· v \· 1. ruling-log (retrieval)        — surface top 3 similar precedents \· \|` · h2:Pipeline (per live gate review)=Precedent's three skills run one pipeline wrapped around board's gate: Write-side (capture) runs standalone whenever any ruling happens; read-side (1–3) wraps review precedents point. · h2:Handoff Rules=**ruling-log case-law-method**: retrieval hands raw precedents; method turns them APPLY/DISTINGUISH conclusions. Retrieval never implies application., **case-law-method consistency-check**: APPLY board wants depart exactly overrule through consistency-check's protocol, never resolved inside case-law-method., **consistency-check ruling-log**: conflict resolution (distinction overrule justification) lands final record; overruled rulings get cross-marked, directions., **precedent board**: precedent informs constrains; board rules; operator decides. Precedent never blocks ruling power making inconsistency visible overrules expensive-in-justification, vetoing., **precedent sentinel**: append-only decision log precedent maintains audit-trail instance; integrity practices follow sentinel's audit-trail-method (immutability, corrections reference). · h2:Precedence Request Matches Multiple Skills=live review runs pipeline order. Standalone questions route verb: *find/what happened* ruling-log; *does apply* case-law-method; *is consistent rule differently* consistency-check. · f=Empty log retrieval returns "no precedent point," pipeline short-circuits, new ruling becomes first record. request doesn't fit, ask consistent skill's clarify-first stance.